The paper focuses on using deep convolutional neural networks to discover and localize semantic concepts within images, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel method for analyzing and visualizing the learned features of the network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions co-segmentation and co-localization, which are tasks commonly studied in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
